    "The study emphasized the importance of accurate modeling considering environmental factors, material properties, and panel design.",
    "By incorporating real-world data from various regions and climates, researchers could optimize solar panel designs and develop effective cooling strategies tailored to specific environmental conditions (Al-Housani et al., 2019).",
    "Table 21 illustrates how solar cell efficiency can vary in different climate zones.",
    "Desert regions experience high temperatures that reduce efficiency, while temperate climates offer more favorable conditions.",
    "Arctic regions may face efficiency challenges due to extreme cold, and tropical climates may contend with high humidity affecting performance."
  ]
